            . On the 16th of March I was waiting to cross <placeName id="t18300415-370-crimeloc2005">Queen-street, Cheapside</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-370-crimeloc2005" type="placeName" value="Queen-street, Cheapside"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-370-crimeloc2005" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-370-off2003 t18300415-370-crimeloc2005"></join>, about half-past eleven o'clock - I did not feel my handkerchief taken, but the officer touched me; I turned, and saw him with the prisoner and this handkerchief in his hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-370-person3043">
                  JOHN 
                  ROE
               <interp inst="t18300415-370-person3043" type="surname" value="ROE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-370-person3043" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-370-person3043" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw the prisoner half a dozen yards on this side Queen-street, with Brown; I saw the prisoner's hand go towards the prosecutor's person, and then saw him putting something under his coat - I went and took him with this handkerchief; I did not see it come from the prosecutor - I believe he was drawn into it - he was not known at all.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. It being my first offence, I hope you will take it into your consideration.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 15.</p>
